{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eaae3422-560e-4c10-a266-e86fc88f22d0","content":"The template looks structurally valid but has a few issues before publishing to NuGet:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation/editor support\n- `groupIdentity` — needed if you plan multiple language variants\n- `preferNameDirectory` — typically `true` for project templates\n\n**Concerns:**\n1. **No `$schema`** reference (e.g., `http://json.schemastore.org/template`)\n2. **Placeholder identity/author** — `\"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"` and `\"My Company\"` look like placeholders, not real values.\n3. **No `description`** field — NuGet gallery will show nothing useful without it.\n4. **No `precedence`** — fine for a first version, but good to set explicitly.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready to publish. At minimum, replace placeholder values with real ones and add a `description` field. The schema and structure are otherwise correct for a `dotnet new` project template.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e8a0672c-773e-417c-9511-61a44707b438","outputTokens":235,"requestId":"E832:B6751:BF1D71:CC121C:6A0AFFC8"},"id":"15b361a4-e873-4e4a-937b-de3f207e62ab","timestamp":"2026-05-18T12:02:25.264Z","parentId":"078e116c-6d9e-41f0-8384-faa4f1fa0e69"}
